Log Analysis for customer qigroup

Welcome to your personalized report for November 9, 2019 - December 8, 2019

This report outlines all visits to all sites within your WP Engine account for the stated time period. Any number of hits from a single IP address within a 24hr period is considered "a visit". A billable visit will be triggered by a browser (person) accessing your site. We exclude bot traffic from billable visits. For more details about how we count visits, you can read more about this in our blog post: How we count "visits".

A word about visits within this report: In many places we have broken down traffic by URL, request type, etc and listed the number of visits we've received. It's worth pointing out that a single visit may be reflected several times within that breakdown but we still will have only counted it once overall against your visit allowance. For example, if a visitor to your site accesses the top 3 most popular URLs, our tables below will reflect a visit for each of those URLs in order to demonstrate popularity, however we will have only recorded a single visit overall against your account. In order to avoid confusion, we label these potentially overlapping visits "popularity".

If you have any questions please see our FAQ: http://wpengine.com/log-analysis-faq
